Biography

CAREER HIGHS: Points 22 points St Cloud State (12-10-22); Rebounds 7 at Mary (2-3-24), at SW Minnesota State (2-21-23), at SW Minnesota State (2-23-24); Assists 3 at CSU Pueblo (11-26-22), Mary (12-9-23); Steals 3 Northern State (12-14-23); 3-pointers made 5 Bemidji State (2-1-24)

2023-24 season

Played in 26 games averaging 7.8 points and 3.0 rebounds per game with 27 assists, 9 steals, and 4 blocked shots.

2022-23 Sophomore Season

Played in all 28 games averaging 8.6 points, 3.4 rebounds per game with 20 assists and 11 steals.

2021-22 (Freshman)

Played in 10 games averaging 1.8 points and 1,0 rebounds with 4 assists and 1 steal.

Prior to MSU

Park Center High School. ...Participated in Football and Soccer. ...B honor roll. ...Parents are John and Kim Cook.

Why I Chose MSU

Felt a strong connection with players and coaches.

Interesting Fact

My two varsity snaps at quarterback resulted in a fumble and a safety.
